# [DNSOP](../wg/dnsop.html)

## Summary

The DNSOP Working Group met at IETF 126 to discuss active working group documents, consider new proposals for adoption, and run a DNS Dispatch session to direct several individual proposals to their appropriate homes. 

Key administrative updates included:
* Publication of RFC 9575 (referenced as "RFC-ninety-five-seventy-five" in slides/discussions).
* Splitting DNSOP into two groups (DNSOP and DNS Commentary) is progressing, with Area Directors finalizing changes before the next IETF.
* An open-source funding announcement by **Karl**, offering grants of up to £15,000/year for individuals and £100,000/year for institutions over three years to maintain open-source DNS software.

Active working group documents `draft-ietf-dnsop-integration`, `draft-ietf-dnsop-dnssec-keyrestore`, and `draft-ietf-dnsop-delegation-mgmt-via-ddns` were presented and are moving toward Working Group Last Call (WGLC). Several new adoptions and dispatches were also progressed.

